title: Vestal drops second straight in tight loss to Corning
text:
Vestal drops second straight in tight loss to Corning 
By wbng sports October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 12:08 AM EDT 
Corning, NY (WBNG Binghamton) Corning stopped Vestal on a fourth quarter two-point conversion that would have tied the game, allowing the Hawks to hold off the Golden Bears, 28-26, Friday night. 
The win moves Corning to 4-1 while Vestal, after losing its first game of the season one week earlier to Maine-Endwell, drops to 3-2 on the season.
